    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You shouldn't install both anaconda 2 and 3 on your system, you should install one and use conda environments if you want to use both Python 2 and 3. \r\nIf you issue a `$ which pip3` you will see that `pip3` is (most likely)  __not__ the pip of anaconda.\r\nTo upgrade Ipython  for anaconda you __must__ use `pip`, and if you want to install in an environment using pip you __must__ `source activate <env>` before installing. "
  },
