    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "To clarify a bit, once you have one version of Anaconda installed, you can create an environment for the other Python by doing:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconda create -n my-py2-env python=2\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat command creates an environment named `my-py2-env` using Python 2. You can activate it in the terminal to use Python 2, or deactivate it to go back to the Anaconda 'root environment'.\r\n\r\nFor more info, see the conda docs @Carreau linked to above."
